Senate President Ahmad Lawan, on Monday, said the National Assembly (NASS) has concluded plans to introduce an annual award for parliamentary reporting. Lawan who spoke as the Chairman of the “Senate Press Corps Awards and Dinner 2021,” held in Abuja, said the gesture is meant to motivate parliamentary reporters to put in their best. He said the National Institute of Democratic and Legislative Studies (NILDS) would henceforth offer a course in parliamentary reporting. He said the course would help build the capacity of journalists reporting the National Assembly.